screen_name: It’s good to be home, how I missed my place and these faces. I am feeling better as each day passes. 7 more days being quarantined then go test again to see if I am Covid19 negative. https://t.co/KLMAr1DUNb

@MarkusMN I’m still hospitalized, I’ll probably be here for another week or so. I keep having some episodes but then they med me up and I’m ok. They just started an IV med for the Covid19 that I have but the MRI and EEG will have to wait till I test negative for the Covid.

This virus is no joke, I’ve been in the hospital for a week come tomorrow. The only symptoms I had was nauseous and a seizure that led to a stroke. I have taken this serious from day 1 and I wear a mask and stayed home until I had to go back to work. Take this serious people.

@QueerMeNow Luckily I am on the mends after being on the IV drug #remdesivir 

My thoughts and prayers goes out to Jessie Colter. Stay strong my friend.
@JerlandBarnett I am getting treatment from an IV drug and today has been my best day thus far.

The week from hell, 2 days ago I had a seizure and Friday morning I suffered a stroke and today I had another episode in which I am a lucky guy after 6 nurses rushed in my room to save me. Later today I tested positive for Covid 19. It’s no joke people, STAY HOME!
